u, A., Simulating Arctic climate warmth and icefield retreat in the last intergalciation (2006) Sci, 311, pp. 1751-1753; Overpeck, J.T., Otto-Bliesner, B.L., Miller, G.H., Muhs, D.R., Alley, R.B., Kiehl, J.T., Paleoclimatic evidence for future ice-sheet instability and rapid sea-level rise (2006) Sci, 311, pp. 1747-1750; Parmesan, C., Climate and species' range (1996) Nature, 382, pp. 765-766; Parmesan, C., Yohe, G., A globally coherent fingerprint of climate change impacts across natural systems (2003) Nature, 421, pp. 37-42; Parmesan, C., Ryrholm, N., Stefanescu, C., Hill, J.K., Thomas, C.D., Descimon, H., Huntley, B., Warren, M., Poleward shift of butterfly species' ranges associated with regional warming (1999) Nature, 399, pp. 579-583; Peters, R.L., Darling, J.D.S., The greenhouse effect and nature reserves (1985) Bioscience, 35, pp. 707-717; Peterson, A.T., Projected climate change effects on Rocky Mountain and Great Plains birds: Generalities of biodiversity consequences (2003) Glob Change Biol, 9, pp. 647-655; Peterson, A.T., Ortega-Huerta, M.A., Bartley, J., Sánchez-Cordero, V., Soberón, J., Buddemeier, R.H., Stockwell, D.R.B., Future projections for Mexican faunas under global climate change scenarios (2002) Nature, 416, pp. 626-629; Peterson, A.T., Tian, H., Martínez-Meyer, E., Soberón, J., Sánchez-Cordero, V., Huntley, B., Modeling distributional shifts of individual species and biomes (2005) Climate Change and Biodiversity, pp. 211-228. , T. E. Lovejoy and L. Hannah (Eds.), New Haven: Yale University Press; Pimm, S.L., Raven, P., Extinction by numbers (2000) Nature, 403, pp. 843-845; Pounds, J.A., Fogden, M.P.L., Campbell, J.H., Biological response to climate change on a tropical mountain (1999) Nature, 398, pp. 611-615; Rignot, E., Kanagaratnam, P., Changes in the velocity structure of the Greenland ice sheet (2006) Science, 311, pp. 986-990; Shepherd, A., Wingham, D., Recent sea-level contributions of the Antarctic and Greenland ice sheets (2007) Sci,